                                                                                    						<textarea rows="12" id="content11" name="detail11" class="wysihtml5 form-control"><p></p><p>After breakfast, our tour guide and driver will pick you up at your&nbsp;hotel and depart for&nbsp;<b>Ayutthaya</b>&nbsp;by air-conditioned car,<br>Ayutthaya the former capital city of Thailand. The first places you visit is&nbsp;Bang Pa-In Summer Palace&nbsp;one of the most beautiful&nbsp;<b>Summer Palace of Thailand</b>.<br>Then follow by&nbsp;<b>Wat Yai Chaimongkhol&nbsp;</b>where you have a chance to sacred one of the biggest Reclining Buddha Image as well and the ruins of the old&nbsp;<b>Royal Grand Palace &amp; Temples</b>. Continue to visit&nbsp;<b>Wat Phra Si Sanphet&nbsp;</b>&amp;&nbsp;<b>Viharn Phra Mongkol Bopit</b>, one of&nbsp;<b>the largest bronze Buddhas</b>&nbsp;in Thailand. Finally,&nbsp;visit&nbsp;<b>Wat Maha That</b>, the heart and soul of the Ayutthaya people.<br>At noon, transfer to the Pier for Cruising down the&nbsp;<b>Chao Phraya River</b>&nbsp;to Bangkok. Certainly, along the River you will have impress &amp; enjoy the rural Thai life along the River. Lunch on board with many varieties of Thai / Inter delicious Buffet. You will arrive in Bangkok by&nbsp;3.30PM. Then transfer to your hotel to relax.&nbsp;<br>Overnight in Bangkok.<br></p><p></p></textarea>
